1
00:00:00,734 --> 00:00:02,736
♪

2
00:00:08,876 --> 00:00:12,179
Narrator: With enyaba in tow
and a new carriage to boot,

3
00:00:12,212 --> 00:00:15,449
jojo and crew arrived
in the coastal town of Karachi,

4
00:00:15,482 --> 00:00:17,985
pakistan’s industrial
and financial center

5
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,721
located
in the indus river delta.

6
00:00:20,754 --> 00:00:22,756
♪

7
00:00:29,897 --> 00:00:31,899
( Singing in Japanese )

8
00:01:05,499 --> 00:01:07,468
♪

9
00:01:07,501 --> 00:01:10,270
( Overlapping chatter )

10
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:16,410
Joseph: Oh.

11
00:01:16,443 --> 00:01:19,079
Hey, a doner kebab joint.

12
00:01:19,112 --> 00:01:21,181
Let’s stop and
get something to eat.

13
00:01:21,215 --> 00:01:23,084
( Slurps )

14
00:01:23,116 --> 00:01:26,286
( Horse neighs )

15
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:28,355
Narrator: The doner kebab,

16
00:01:28,388 --> 00:01:31,124
it’s been called the hamburger
of the middle east.

17
00:01:31,158 --> 00:01:33,794
A slab of meat
is placed on a spit,

18
00:01:33,827 --> 00:01:36,096
its outer layer roasting
as it turns.

19
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:38,365
Before long,
the meat is cooked, sliced,

20
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:41,368
and served with any number
of sides and condiments.

21
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:43,003
- Joseph: Excuse me, sir.
- Vendor: Eh?

22
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:44,538
Joseph: I’d like five of those.

23
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:46,106
Vendor: That’ll be 1,000 yen.

24
00:01:46,139 --> 00:01:48,008
Joseph: 1,000 yen?

25
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:49,242
Narrator: In the middle east,

26
00:01:49,276 --> 00:01:51,245
Japanese and western
business practices

27
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:53,046
are by no means universal.

28
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:56,050
Namely, prices change
and are open to negotiation.

29
00:01:56,083 --> 00:01:58,319
With no understanding
of how to haggle

30
00:01:58,352 --> 00:02:00,588
or how to value goods for sale,

31
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:04,058
first-time visitors can become
easy targets for exploitation,

32
00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:07,828
but here, people don’t see such
exploitation as a bad thing.

33
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:11,431
The swindled are deserving
of the label fool, not victim.

34
00:02:11,465 --> 00:02:14,068
Haggling takes guts
and ingenuity.

35
00:02:14,101 --> 00:02:15,436
Joseph: Really?

36
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:17,972
Narrator: The first step
is the art of the bluff.

37
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:20,074
Make it clear
you see through the trick.

38
00:02:20,107 --> 00:02:21,609
Let him know you’re no slouch.

39
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:23,077
( Joseph laughs )

40
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:24,411
Don’t mock me now.

41
00:02:24,444 --> 00:02:27,347
That’s far too much
for a handful of kebabs.

42
00:02:27,381 --> 00:02:30,084
Narrator: A hearty laugh
always helps. Then...

43
00:02:30,117 --> 00:02:32,252
Vendor: How much
would you buy ’em for?

44
00:02:32,286 --> 00:02:34,555
Narrator: The merchant
will test the waters.

45
00:02:34,588 --> 00:02:37,024
Joseph: Make it
250 yen for five.

46
00:02:37,057 --> 00:02:40,394
Narrator: In return,
you throw out a price so low,

47
00:02:40,427 --> 00:02:43,330
you can’t help but blush.
And then...

48
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:46,199
( Vendor laughs )

49
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:49,369
Narrator: He’ll act as if
you have no sense at all.

50
00:02:49,403 --> 00:02:50,604
Catching on?

51
00:02:50,637 --> 00:02:52,439
Vendor: If I sold them
for that cheap,

52
00:02:52,472 --> 00:02:55,175
i’d be out on the streets,
and my wife and seven children

53
00:02:55,209 --> 00:02:57,278
would starve to death. ( Gags )

54
00:02:57,311 --> 00:03:00,147
Narrator: Then he’ll gesture
the old throat slash,

55
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:02,916
but you can’t
give up the fight just yet.

56
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:05,486
Joseph: Then maybe i’ll
just buy them somewhere else.

57
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:07,154
Narrator: Pretend
that you’re leaving.

58
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,222
Vendor: Okay, friend, you win.

59
00:03:09,256 --> 00:03:11,058
I very much like foreigners.

60
00:03:11,091 --> 00:03:13,293
I’ll sell you five for 700 yen.

61
00:03:13,327 --> 00:03:15,229
Narrator: He’ll try to stop you.

62
00:03:15,262 --> 00:03:17,431
Joseph: Then make it 300.

63
00:03:17,464 --> 00:03:19,166
Narrator:
Let the haggling begin!

64
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:21,535
- Vendor: 600!
- Joseph: 350!

65
00:03:21,568 --> 00:03:23,470
- Vendor: 550!
- Joseph: 400!

66
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:24,505
Vendor: 450!

67
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:27,174
Both: 425!

68
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,909
Joseph: I’ll take ’em.

69
00:03:28,942 --> 00:03:31,978
All right. I got them for less
than half his original price.

70
00:03:32,012 --> 00:03:35,549
Take that.
I made out like a bandit.

71
00:03:35,582 --> 00:03:37,484
Narrator: And just
as you think you won...

72
00:03:37,518 --> 00:03:41,522
Vendor: I usually
sell five for 150 yen.

73
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:43,057
Bye-bye. Thank you, sir.

74
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:45,326
♪

75
00:03:45,359 --> 00:03:46,961
Joseph: Huh?

76
00:03:46,994 --> 00:03:48,629
♪

77
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,101
- Holy crap!
- Polnareff: Huh?

78
00:03:54,134 --> 00:03:55,602
Joseph: Turn around!
That old lady’s awake.

79
00:03:55,636 --> 00:03:56,604
( Both gasp )

80
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:58,639
( Enyaba shuddering )

81
00:04:04,011 --> 00:04:05,713
I--i promise you...

82
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:09,183
I haven’t said anything
to any of them, I swear.

83
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:11,218
Wh-why are you here?

84
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:13,286
What could
you possibly want with me?

85
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,622
Did you think
I would actually tell them

86
00:04:15,656 --> 00:04:17,258
the secret of lord dio’s stand?

87
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:20,127
I am and shall always be
his loyal servant.

88
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,161
Joseph: Eh?

89
00:04:22,196 --> 00:04:24,732
♪

90
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,533
( Men gasping )

91
00:04:32,673 --> 00:04:34,241
( Worms chitter )

92
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,375
( Enyaba shuddering )

93
00:04:35,409 --> 00:04:37,778
( Screams )

94
00:04:39,513 --> 00:04:42,416
( Horse neighs )

95
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:44,518
Polnareff: Gross.

96
00:04:44,551 --> 00:04:47,087
What are they?
Some kind of worms?

97
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:50,357
Enyaba: Why?
I have done nothing wrong!

98
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:52,092
Why have you come here
to kill me?!

99
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:57,030
Stand user: Lord dio
places his trust in no one,

100
00:04:57,064 --> 00:04:58,332
not even you, enyaba.

101
00:04:58,365 --> 00:05:00,167
That is why.

102
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:04,438
And it’s my job to make sure
that you never speak again.

103
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:06,707
As for the rest of you...

104
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:11,311
The only way
you’re leaving is in pieces.

105
00:05:12,513 --> 00:05:14,482
( Enyaba gags )

106
00:05:14,515 --> 00:05:15,483
Polnareff: Memere!

107
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:17,284
( Enyaba screams )

108
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:19,186
Joseph: What?

109
00:05:20,521 --> 00:05:22,723
Dan: You can call me Dan,

110
00:05:22,756 --> 00:05:24,658
Dan of steel.

111
00:05:24,691 --> 00:05:27,327
My stand represents
the one and only lovers card.

112
00:05:27,361 --> 00:05:30,397
I will see to it
that you all meet the same fate

113
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:31,798
as that pathetic witch enyaba.

114
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:33,367
Polnareff: How could you?!

115
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,602
That old lady was one
of your own, you son of a--

116
00:05:35,636 --> 00:05:36,704
memere!

117
00:05:36,737 --> 00:05:37,705
( Enyaba gags )

118
00:05:37,738 --> 00:05:40,774
Lies. Lies.

119
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:43,777
These are all lies.

120
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:45,345
This isn’t happening.

121
00:05:45,379 --> 00:05:47,448
Lord dio would never
do this to me.

122
00:05:47,481 --> 00:05:50,384
I am his loyal servant, loyal.

123
00:05:50,417 --> 00:05:52,753
Kakyoin: These things
coming out of her body

124
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:54,488
they’re definitely
not some stand.

125
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:57,557
Don’t you see it?
They’re actual tentacles.

126
00:05:57,591 --> 00:06:00,427
Enyaba: I have dedicated
everything to him.

127
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:03,463
Lord dio would never
do me such harm.

128
00:06:03,497 --> 00:06:06,233
He’d never plant
a flesh bud in me.

129
00:06:06,266 --> 00:06:07,634
Kakyoin: What did she say?

130
00:06:07,668 --> 00:06:11,572
Lord dio is
my only reason for living.

131
00:06:11,605 --> 00:06:14,775
We trust each other
wholeheartedly. ( Gags )

132
00:06:14,808 --> 00:06:16,076
Polnareff: Hold on!

133
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:17,377
( Grunts )

134
00:06:21,148 --> 00:06:23,183
( Worms squeal )

135
00:06:23,217 --> 00:06:24,351
Joseph: See that?

136
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:26,386
The sun just disintegrated them!

137
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:29,657
The flesh bud, it’s made
out of dio’s own cells.

138
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:31,125
Dan: Precisely.

139
00:06:31,158 --> 00:06:33,594
I must say you are
quite the perceptive one.

140
00:06:33,627 --> 00:06:35,395
Since you’re so astute,
i’ll continue.

141
00:06:35,429 --> 00:06:38,165
This is what a full-grown
flesh bud looks like.

142
00:06:38,198 --> 00:06:40,500
I want to kill her,
not control her,

143
00:06:40,534 --> 00:06:43,137
so I just grew it
inside the old bag.

144
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:46,140
Enyaba, you may be the very one

145
00:06:46,173 --> 00:06:48,442
who told lord dio
about the stands,

146
00:06:48,475 --> 00:06:51,345
but you’re a fool to think that
a man with such complete power

147
00:06:51,378 --> 00:06:54,147
would ever trust
a feeble old woman like you.

148
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:55,482
- ( Enyaba gagging )
- Dan: Unfortunately,

149
00:06:55,516 --> 00:06:57,752
it’s a point
you failed to realize.

150
00:06:57,784 --> 00:06:59,452
Joseph: Old lady!

151
00:06:59,486 --> 00:07:02,189
What’s the true identity
of dio’s stand?

152
00:07:02,222 --> 00:07:03,857
- Dan: Huh?
- ( All gasp )

153
00:07:03,891 --> 00:07:05,359
Joseph: Tell us!

154
00:07:05,392 --> 00:07:07,361
You placed all your hope in dio.

155
00:07:07,394 --> 00:07:09,496
You trusted him
with your life and your son’s.

156
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:11,232
And now after
all you’ve sacrificed,

157
00:07:11,265 --> 00:07:13,834
you know he’s not the man
you thought he was.

158
00:07:13,867 --> 00:07:15,235
You know i’m right.

159
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:17,838
We must defeat dio,
no matter the cost.

160
00:07:17,871 --> 00:07:19,406
You have to tell us.

161
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,541
We need to know!

162
00:07:21,575 --> 00:07:24,244
Tell us what we need to know
about dio’s stand

163
00:07:24,278 --> 00:07:25,546
before it’s too late!

164
00:07:27,247 --> 00:07:30,584
Enyaba: D-dio...

165
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:31,852
My lord.

166
00:07:37,691 --> 00:07:39,159
♪

167
00:07:39,193 --> 00:07:40,594
( Gasps )

168
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:44,898
He believes in me, so i’ll
serve him even in death.

169
00:07:44,932 --> 00:07:47,168
- I won’t betray him.
- Joseph: Huh?

170
00:07:47,201 --> 00:07:49,470
( Enyaba sighs )

171
00:07:51,905 --> 00:07:55,242
Joseph: Oh, god!

172
00:07:55,275 --> 00:07:57,310
( Dan laughing )

173
00:08:00,581 --> 00:08:03,384
How pathetic. ( Laughs )

174
00:08:03,417 --> 00:08:06,620
It’s laughable
how sad that old woman was.

175
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:08,622
But the very depth
of her trust in him

176
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:10,457
should tell you something.

177
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,593
Lord dio’s evil charm is more
powerful than you can imagine.

178
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:15,395
( Laughs )

179
00:08:15,429 --> 00:08:18,332
♪

180
00:08:21,535 --> 00:08:24,204
( Sips )

181
00:08:24,238 --> 00:08:27,208
Polnareff: The old woman
may have had it out for us,

182
00:08:27,241 --> 00:08:28,542
but she was misled

183
00:08:28,575 --> 00:08:30,677
and sure as hell
didn’t deserve that death.

184
00:08:30,711 --> 00:08:32,913
- I’ll see you join her.
- ( Joseph grunts )

185
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:35,549
Kakyoin: Four against one,
but we won’t hold back.

186
00:08:35,582 --> 00:08:36,783
Prepare yourself, Dan.

187
00:08:37,818 --> 00:08:39,787
Jotaro: On your feet.

188
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:41,855
( Dan sips )

189
00:08:43,824 --> 00:08:45,292
Jotaro: Hey, jackass,

190
00:08:45,325 --> 00:08:48,395
stop trying to act cool,
and get up and fight.

191
00:08:48,428 --> 00:08:51,398
This is going down,
whether you want it or not.

192
00:08:51,431 --> 00:08:52,565
Dan: Go ahead.

193
00:08:52,599 --> 00:08:54,267
But you can’t touch me.

194
00:08:54,301 --> 00:08:57,371
I’m Dan of steel, and none
of you can take me down.

195
00:08:57,404 --> 00:08:58,605
You don’t have what it takes.

196
00:08:58,639 --> 00:08:59,607
Star platinum: Ora!

197
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,608
( Dan yells )

198
00:09:00,641 --> 00:09:02,276
( Joseph yells )

199
00:09:02,309 --> 00:09:03,744
Jotaro: What the?

200
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:06,346
Polnareff: W-what happened,
Mr. Joestar?

201
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:08,582
He flew back just like that guy.

202
00:09:08,615 --> 00:09:10,016
( Dan groans )

203
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:11,552
You’re an utter fool.

204
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:14,855
I was about to explain
my powers when you hit me.

205
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:16,656
That impatience
nearly killed your grandfather.

206
00:09:16,690 --> 00:09:18,492
I suggest you listen next time.

207
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,293
Jotaro: Huh?

208
00:09:20,327 --> 00:09:23,030
Dan: Listen. My job’s not over.

209
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,766
I have other important business
to attend to.

210
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:28,302
You really think
I would show my face here

211
00:09:28,335 --> 00:09:30,270
just to kill enyaba? ( Spits )

212
00:09:30,304 --> 00:09:32,339
Joseph: You--you damn bastard.

213
00:09:32,372 --> 00:09:35,842
You told us that your stand
is the lovers. Isn’t that right?

214
00:09:35,876 --> 00:09:38,679
So tell us!
What the hell does it do?!

215
00:09:38,712 --> 00:09:41,415
Dan: What’s the point
in telling you now?

216
00:09:41,448 --> 00:09:44,518
The battle’s already begun,
Mr. Joestar.

217
00:09:44,551 --> 00:09:45,819
( Men gasping )

218
00:09:45,853 --> 00:09:47,722
Dan: You’re all simpletons.

219
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:49,823
You do know,
no matter how hard you look,

220
00:09:49,857 --> 00:09:51,726
you won’t be able
to see my stand.

221
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:52,959
( Boy humming a tune )

222
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:55,028
- Dan: Hey, half pint.
- Boy: Hmm?

223
00:09:55,062 --> 00:09:57,064
Dan: You want some cash?
It’s all yours

224
00:09:57,097 --> 00:09:59,633
if you can hit me in the leg
with that broom.

225
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:00,634
Boy: Whoa.

226
00:10:00,667 --> 00:10:02,302
Oh.

227
00:10:02,336 --> 00:10:03,671
Wha?

228
00:10:03,704 --> 00:10:05,940
Joseph: What?
But why would he...

229
00:10:06,974 --> 00:10:09,376
Dan: Now hit me!

230
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:10,944
( Joseph yells )

231
00:10:10,978 --> 00:10:13,347
Kakyoin: The hell? Now what?

232
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:14,448
( Joseph gasps )

233
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:16,416
It--it hurts!

234
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:19,353
I don’t get it!
It’s like I broke my leg!

235
00:10:19,386 --> 00:10:21,521
You mean you still
haven’t figured it out?

236
00:10:21,555 --> 00:10:23,490
That’s so disappointing.

237
00:10:23,524 --> 00:10:26,694
My stand can’t be seen, because
it’s rooted firmly inside you.

238
00:10:26,727 --> 00:10:28,729
The moment enyaba died,
it entered you.

239
00:10:28,762 --> 00:10:30,831
It got to your brain
through your ear,

240
00:10:30,864 --> 00:10:32,733
and that’s how i’ll get to you.

241
00:10:32,766 --> 00:10:34,067
Joseph: What?!

242
00:10:40,607 --> 00:10:44,344
Dan: My stand and I
are connected, just like yours.

243
00:10:44,378 --> 00:10:48,515
If my stand gets hurt, so do I,
and the reverse is also true.

244
00:10:48,549 --> 00:10:50,117
( The lovers squeals )

245
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:53,420
Dan: You’re utterly helpless.
If you so much as scratch me,

246
00:10:53,453 --> 00:10:56,056
in that instant,
my stand will react to my pain

247
00:10:56,089 --> 00:10:57,791
by going berserk in your head

248
00:10:57,824 --> 00:11:00,026
and inflicting
the same agony on you.

249
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:03,530
Not only that, it will deliver
a pain several times greater.

250
00:11:03,564 --> 00:11:05,533
Now i’ll say it once more.

251
00:11:05,566 --> 00:11:07,068
Alone or together,

252
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:09,569
you won’t be able to lay
a single finger on me.

253
00:11:09,603 --> 00:11:11,738
( Joseph gasps )

254
00:11:11,772 --> 00:11:13,073
Dan: Plus, the lovers has taken

255
00:11:13,106 --> 00:11:15,775
one of lord dio’s flesh buds
into your body.

256
00:11:15,809 --> 00:11:18,045
It’s growing in your brain
as we speak.

257
00:11:18,078 --> 00:11:20,147
Just like it did to enyaba,

258
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,816
it’ll devour you
from the inside out.

259
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:24,151
( Boy chuckles )

260
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:26,153
( Joseph screams )

261
00:11:26,186 --> 00:11:27,888
- ( Dan chuckles )
- ( Boy laughs )

262
00:11:27,921 --> 00:11:30,724
Dan: I don’t recall asking you
to strike me again,

263
00:11:30,757 --> 00:11:32,058
you stupid little brat!

264
00:11:32,092 --> 00:11:33,961
( Boy yelps )

265
00:11:33,994 --> 00:11:35,963
( Gasping )

266
00:11:35,996 --> 00:11:39,132
Dan: Well, to be honest,
my stand, the lovers,

267
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:42,002
isn’t as strong
as you might think it’d be.

268
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:43,470
It doesn’t have the strength

269
00:11:43,504 --> 00:11:45,606
to move even
a single strand of hair,

270
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:47,875
making it
the world’s weakest stand.

271
00:11:47,908 --> 00:11:49,676
However...

272
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,145
Power isn’t necessary

273
00:11:51,178 --> 00:11:54,515
if all you want to do
is kill your opponent.

274
00:11:54,548 --> 00:11:56,150
Do you understand, gentlemen?

275
00:11:56,183 --> 00:11:58,185
♪

276
00:12:01,822 --> 00:12:03,357
Unfortunate happens,

277
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,359
like I get into an accident,

278
00:12:05,392 --> 00:12:08,495
a baseball hits me,
or I just trip and fall.

279
00:12:08,529 --> 00:12:12,466
How do you think that would
affect you, Mr. Joestar?

280
00:12:12,499 --> 00:12:14,201
Dan: I might get banged up some,

281
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:17,370
but your body would suffer
far greater pain than mine.

282
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:18,705
( Cracks knuckles )

283
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:20,507
Joseph: What the? How?

284
00:12:20,541 --> 00:12:23,611
How am I feeling your knuckles
cracking in my prosthetic hand?

285
00:12:23,644 --> 00:12:25,579
Dan: You’ve got
10 minutes, old man.

286
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:27,848
Then your brain
will be eaten through,

287
00:12:27,881 --> 00:12:30,350
and you’ll be a corpse
like enyaba.

288
00:12:30,384 --> 00:12:32,753
( Jotaro growls )

289
00:12:32,786 --> 00:12:35,489
Kakyoin: Jotaro, calm down.
Don’t do anything rash.

290
00:12:35,522 --> 00:12:36,757
Jotaro: Sorry, but no.

291
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:38,892
I’m gonna kill
this damn tool so quickly,

292
00:12:38,926 --> 00:12:41,162
he won’t have enough time
to feel pain.

293
00:12:41,195 --> 00:12:43,597
( Joseph groaning )

294
00:12:48,836 --> 00:12:51,238
Dan: Kill me
before I feel it, huh?

295
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:53,774
Sounds interesting.
Do it, then.

296
00:12:53,807 --> 00:12:55,609
I wanna see what happens.

297
00:12:55,642 --> 00:12:58,411
What are you waiting for,
jotaro?

298
00:12:58,445 --> 00:12:59,913
Come on. Let’s see it.

299
00:12:59,947 --> 00:13:02,450
Just what were you
planning to strike?

300
00:13:02,482 --> 00:13:05,218
Tell me. My face?
Or maybe my throat?

301
00:13:05,252 --> 00:13:07,421
♪

302
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:09,156
What? You mad?

303
00:13:09,189 --> 00:13:10,257
Let’s see what’ll happen.

304
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,359
Don’t back down on me now, man.

305
00:13:12,392 --> 00:13:15,428
Why don’t you try busting
a hole through my chest?

306
00:13:15,462 --> 00:13:18,365
Or how ’bout you give up
on using your stand,

307
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:20,767
and crack my head open
with a rock?

308
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:22,936
This one looks
like a prime specimen.

309
00:13:22,970 --> 00:13:25,840
It sure looks
big enough for the job.

310
00:13:25,873 --> 00:13:27,641
Hmm.

311
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:32,245
Jotaro: You do not want
to underestimate me, pretty boy.

312
00:13:32,279 --> 00:13:36,183
When I say i’m gonna
do something, I do it.

313
00:13:36,216 --> 00:13:38,285
( Dan gasps )

314
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:39,853
( Joseph groaning )

315
00:13:39,887 --> 00:13:41,355
( Jotaro yells )

316
00:13:41,388 --> 00:13:43,590
Kakyoin: Jotaro, don’t do it!

317
00:13:43,624 --> 00:13:46,327
We’ve already seen
how effective his power is.

318
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,395
Are you trying to kill
your own grandfather?

319
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:50,430
Polnareff: Uh, this is
jotaro we’re talking about.

320
00:13:50,464 --> 00:13:51,465
He might be.

321
00:13:51,498 --> 00:13:53,266
( Jotaro sputters )

322
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,602
Dan: You dumb,
good-for-nothing punk.

323
00:13:58,705 --> 00:14:00,874
Oh?

324
00:14:03,377 --> 00:14:04,545
( Jotaro groans )

325
00:14:04,578 --> 00:14:05,679
Joseph: Jotaro!

326
00:14:06,947 --> 00:14:10,250
Dan: Don’t you toy with me,
you bastard.

327
00:14:10,284 --> 00:14:12,753
After the geezer kicks
the bucket, you’re next.

328
00:14:12,786 --> 00:14:14,354
Kakyoin: Look out!

329
00:14:14,388 --> 00:14:16,523
( Jotaro groans )

330
00:14:16,557 --> 00:14:19,660
Dan: It’ll be your brain that I
send the lovers in to kill.

331
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:22,229
Joseph: Stop. What the hell
do you think you’re doing?

332
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:24,731
( Dan laughs )

333
00:14:24,765 --> 00:14:27,334
( Jotaro growling )

334
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:28,935
Joseph: This is just insane.

335
00:14:28,969 --> 00:14:32,339
My grandson is being
beaten up to save me.

336
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:34,407
We’re completely
at this guy’s mercy.

337
00:14:34,441 --> 00:14:37,010
I can’t do anything
while it’s in my brain.

338
00:14:37,044 --> 00:14:38,812
I remember when that poison ring

339
00:14:38,846 --> 00:14:41,248
was placed
around my aorta long ago,

340
00:14:41,281 --> 00:14:42,549
but think, Joseph.

341
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:45,019
There’s got to be
something you can do.

342
00:14:45,052 --> 00:14:46,053
( Gasps )

343
00:14:47,387 --> 00:14:49,556
( Kakyoin grunts )

344
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:50,624
Dan: Hmm?

345
00:14:54,361 --> 00:14:56,296
Polnareff: H-hey!

346
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:59,567
Kakyoin: Jotaro, keep him away
from Mr. Joestar at all costs!

347
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:03,370
We’re gonna try and get as far
away from him as possible!

348
00:15:05,305 --> 00:15:07,474
Dan: I see.
So that’s your plan?

349
00:15:07,508 --> 00:15:10,344
Putting some distance
between me and the old man

350
00:15:10,377 --> 00:15:13,280
might make my stand’s power
vanish without a trace?

351
00:15:13,313 --> 00:15:15,382
Sorry, but my stand’s
physical weakness

352
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:17,651
is made up for in other ways.

353
00:15:17,684 --> 00:15:19,653
The lovers
may be physically weak,

354
00:15:19,686 --> 00:15:22,722
but its range is farther
than any stand in existence.

355
00:15:22,756 --> 00:15:24,958
It doesn’t matter
how far they run.

356
00:15:24,992 --> 00:15:28,529
Their lives are forfeit
as long as it remains in a host.

357
00:15:28,562 --> 00:15:29,563
Hmm?

358
00:15:30,597 --> 00:15:32,666
( Gasps ) What’s up?

359
00:15:32,699 --> 00:15:34,634
Hey, jotaro, i’m talking to you.

360
00:15:34,668 --> 00:15:36,837
It’s impolite
not to look at people

361
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:39,439
when they’re speaking to you.
Look at me!

362
00:15:40,474 --> 00:15:41,875
Jotaro: What’s wrong?

363
00:15:41,909 --> 00:15:43,944
You sound like you’re
starting to lose your cool.

364
00:15:43,977 --> 00:15:45,779
Dan: What’s your plan?

365
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:48,515
Follow me around
’til grandpa Joseph keels over?

366
00:15:48,549 --> 00:15:49,750
Sounds like a blast.

367
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:51,785
Jotaro: Dan of steel, was it?

368
00:15:51,818 --> 00:15:55,355
I’ll make you pay for this.
Just a matter of when.

369
00:15:55,389 --> 00:15:56,957
( Dan chuckles )

370
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:00,961
( Laughs )

371
00:16:00,994 --> 00:16:03,730
Well, if you’re gonna
stick around for a while,

372
00:16:03,764 --> 00:16:06,400
I might as well help myself
to your wallet.

373
00:16:07,401 --> 00:16:09,470
( Click )

374
00:16:11,972 --> 00:16:13,807
Nothing but chump change, huh?

375
00:16:13,841 --> 00:16:16,110
Though I didn’t expect
a guy like you

376
00:16:16,143 --> 00:16:17,811
to be sporting a tag heuer.

377
00:16:17,845 --> 00:16:19,947
I’ll be borrowing this.

378
00:16:24,618 --> 00:16:26,453
( Kakyoin panting )

379
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:28,121
There!

380
00:16:28,155 --> 00:16:29,990
An electronics store.

381
00:16:30,023 --> 00:16:32,592
Mr. Joestar, they have tvs.

382
00:16:32,626 --> 00:16:35,362
Polnareff: Yeah, so?
Why does that matter now?

383
00:16:35,395 --> 00:16:36,630
Joseph: Come on, polnareff.

384
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:38,598
Did you really think
we were running away?

385
00:16:38,632 --> 00:16:41,802
I’m going to fight this blasted
stand that’s inside my head.

386
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:43,804
Polnareff: Fight? Mon dieu, non.

387
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:45,439
Kakyoin: We only have
a few minutes,

388
00:16:45,472 --> 00:16:47,607
and we’re gonna need your help
to pull this off.

389
00:16:47,641 --> 00:16:48,609
Polnareff: Huh?

390
00:16:48,642 --> 00:16:52,613
Joseph: Hermit purple!

391
00:17:00,521 --> 00:17:02,790
- Kakyoin: That’s it!
- Joseph: Oh, no!

392
00:17:02,823 --> 00:17:04,458
I hoped he was bluffing.

393
00:17:04,491 --> 00:17:06,827
How the hell did he get
inside my brain so damn quickly?

394
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,862
Polnareff: Wow.
If I hadn’t seen it myself,

395
00:17:08,896 --> 00:17:10,531
I wouldn’t have believed it.

396
00:17:10,564 --> 00:17:13,067
At least now we know for sure
that it’s in there.

397
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:16,503
But I still don’t see how we’re
going to destroy the thing

398
00:17:16,537 --> 00:17:19,173
kakyoin: By having our stands
enter Mr. Joestar’s ear canal

399
00:17:19,206 --> 00:17:20,941
to find and destroy the monster.

400
00:17:20,974 --> 00:17:22,576
( Polnareff gasps )
Are you crazy?

401
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:24,945
Kakyoin: Stands are simply
materializations of energy.

402
00:17:24,978 --> 00:17:26,646
We should be able
to shrink them.

403
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,515
Polnareff: You don’t know that.

404
00:17:28,549 --> 00:17:30,684
Joseph: Hey, try not to break
anything while you’re in there.

405
00:17:30,717 --> 00:17:33,687
Kakyoin: There’s no time.
We’re going in now, polnareff.

406
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,488
Polnareff: A-all right.

407
00:17:35,522 --> 00:17:37,457
Kakyoin: Hierophant green!

408
00:17:37,491 --> 00:17:39,693
Polnareff: Silver chariot!

409
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:41,127
Smaller.

410
00:17:45,199 --> 00:17:47,201
Kakyoin: Get smaller.

411
00:17:47,234 --> 00:17:49,870
We’re going to be entering
a blood vessel.

412
00:17:49,903 --> 00:17:50,904
Polnareff: R-right.

413
00:17:50,938 --> 00:17:53,507
♪

414
00:17:57,845 --> 00:17:59,013
Dan: A drainage ditch.

415
00:17:59,046 --> 00:18:00,681
This could be fun.

416
00:18:00,714 --> 00:18:03,984
I’d try to jump it, but if
I trip and twist my ankle,

417
00:18:04,017 --> 00:18:06,486
it could be real bad
for old man joestar.

418
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:09,723
Walking all the way to that
bridge would be such a bother.

419
00:18:09,756 --> 00:18:11,491
I’ve got an idea.

420
00:18:11,525 --> 00:18:14,795
Lie down across this ditch,
and make yourself into a bridge.

421
00:18:14,828 --> 00:18:17,764
I’ll just walk on you
to get across.

422
00:18:18,765 --> 00:18:20,066
What now?

423
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:22,102
You don’t want to be
my bridge or something?

424
00:18:22,135 --> 00:18:23,536
Jotaro: Ah, shut up.

425
00:18:23,570 --> 00:18:24,938
The hell do you
keep yammerin’ about?

426
00:18:24,972 --> 00:18:28,108
Dan: I said
make yourself into a bridge!

427
00:18:28,141 --> 00:18:30,510
You good-for-nothing,
arrogant prick!

428
00:18:30,544 --> 00:18:31,879
( Joseph screams )

429
00:18:31,912 --> 00:18:33,680
Polnareff: What?!
What’s the matter?

430
00:18:33,714 --> 00:18:34,715
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar.

431
00:18:34,748 --> 00:18:36,683
Joseph: M-my leg,

432
00:18:36,717 --> 00:18:38,252
i-it’s going numb.

433
00:18:38,285 --> 00:18:39,720
( Both gasp )

434
00:18:39,753 --> 00:18:41,955
Joseph: Damn it, jotaro.

435
00:18:41,989 --> 00:18:44,124
What the hell are you doing?

436
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:49,129
Dan: Aw, don’t look
so upset, jotaro.

437
00:18:49,163 --> 00:18:51,866
( Chuckles )

438
00:18:51,899 --> 00:18:54,502
♪

439
00:18:54,535 --> 00:18:55,770
( Jotaro grunts )

440
00:19:00,274 --> 00:19:01,509
Dan: Come on.

441
00:19:01,542 --> 00:19:03,577
I don’t have all day, you know.

442
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:05,779
( Jotaro growls )

443
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:15,322
( Dan chuckles ) Good.

444
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:18,825
( Jotaro growls )

445
00:19:24,631 --> 00:19:28,568
Dan: You’re a rather
sturdy bridge, aren’t you?

446
00:19:28,602 --> 00:19:30,671
Boing, boing, boing.

447
00:19:30,704 --> 00:19:32,606
Impressive.

448
00:19:33,607 --> 00:19:35,642
Hold on.

449
00:19:35,676 --> 00:19:37,878
Almost there.

450
00:19:39,246 --> 00:19:41,248
( Jotaro grunting )

451
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:46,620
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar,
I think the stand is here.

452
00:19:46,653 --> 00:19:48,922
Hiding around the thalamus
makes the most sense.

453
00:19:48,956 --> 00:19:51,158
That’s the point
where the nervous system begins.

454
00:19:51,191 --> 00:19:53,727
Polnareff and I will enter
a blood vessel

455
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,095
from inside your inner ear,

456
00:19:55,128 --> 00:19:57,631
then swim through the veins
toward the brainstem.

457
00:19:57,664 --> 00:20:01,334
But to do that, we need to tear
the wall of the blood vessel.

458
00:20:01,368 --> 00:20:02,803
Joseph: Hey, hold on.

459
00:20:02,836 --> 00:20:04,237
You’re using your stands.

460
00:20:04,271 --> 00:20:07,040
Can’t you just slip through it
without cutting me?

461
00:20:07,074 --> 00:20:09,743
Kakyoin: At this size,
it’s not possible.

462
00:20:09,776 --> 00:20:11,978
The blood vessel’s wall
is too thick.

463
00:20:12,012 --> 00:20:14,014
The slit will be microscopic,

464
00:20:14,047 --> 00:20:17,050
so there’ll be no hemorrhaging
to worry about.

465
00:20:17,084 --> 00:20:18,919
The only other issue is time.

466
00:20:18,952 --> 00:20:21,321
Cutting through a blood vessel
or nerve right now

467
00:20:21,355 --> 00:20:22,957
will take several minutes
at least.

468
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,191
Otherwise, the lovers

469
00:20:24,224 --> 00:20:26,159
would have already
done its damage by now.

470
00:20:26,193 --> 00:20:29,196
Though, in all probability,
it may have already started.

471
00:20:29,229 --> 00:20:30,964
( Joseph gasps )

472
00:20:30,998 --> 00:20:34,602
Polnareff: Keeping our stands
this tiny is really exhausting.

473
00:20:34,635 --> 00:20:37,905
It’s taking a ton of stand power
just to get where we can fight.

474
00:20:39,072 --> 00:20:40,941
Silver chariot: On y va!

475
00:20:43,644 --> 00:20:46,814
Joseph: Oh, my god!

476
00:20:46,847 --> 00:20:49,383
I-I really don’t feel so well.

477
00:20:49,416 --> 00:20:51,785
♪

478
00:20:55,889 --> 00:20:57,891
( Dan humming a tune )

479
00:21:08,402 --> 00:21:10,404
♪

480
00:21:22,249 --> 00:21:24,852
♪ All the old paintings
on the tomb ♪

481
00:21:24,885 --> 00:21:27,121
♪ they do the sand dance,
don’t you know ♪

482
00:21:27,154 --> 00:21:28,255
♪ if they move too quick

483
00:21:28,288 --> 00:21:29,823
♪ oh, whey, oh

484
00:21:29,857 --> 00:21:31,792
♪ they’re falling down
like a domino ♪

485
00:21:31,825 --> 00:21:34,127
♪ all the bazaar men
by the nile ♪

486
00:21:34,161 --> 00:21:36,230
♪ they got the money on a bet

487
00:21:36,263 --> 00:21:37,431
♪ gold crocodiles

488
00:21:37,464 --> 00:21:38,966
♪ oh, whey, oh

489
00:21:38,999 --> 00:21:41,034
♪ they snap their teeth
on your cigarette ♪

490
00:21:41,068 --> 00:21:43,170
♪ foreign types
with the hookah pipes say ♪

491
00:21:43,203 --> 00:21:45,439
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

492
00:21:45,472 --> 00:21:49,176
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

493
00:21:50,277 --> 00:21:52,913
♪ walk like an Egyptian

494
00:22:04,157 --> 00:22:06,860
♪ The blond waitresses
take their trays ♪

495
00:22:06,894 --> 00:22:08,963
♪ they spin around,
and they cross the floor ♪

496
00:22:08,996 --> 00:22:10,231
♪ they’ve got the moves

497
00:22:10,264 --> 00:22:11,232
♪ oh, whey, oh

498
00:22:11,265 --> 00:22:12,266
♪ you drop your drink

499
00:22:12,299 --> 00:22:13,767
♪ then they bring you more

500
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,036
♪ all the school kids
so sick of books ♪

501
00:22:16,069 --> 00:22:18,238
♪ they like the punk
and the metal band ♪

502
00:22:18,272 --> 00:22:19,473
♪ when the buzzer rings

503
00:22:19,506 --> 00:22:20,974
♪ oh, whey, oh

504
00:22:21,008 --> 00:22:22,977
♪ they’re walking
like an Egyptian ♪

505
00:22:23,010 --> 00:22:25,112
♪ all the kids
